                        <msContents>
                            
                            <summary>Malay demonology and magic. Account of the origins of different ghosts.</summary>
                            <textLang mainLang="ms">Malay</textLang>
                            
                            <msItem xml:id="Wellcome_Malay_3_Part_2_Item_1">
                                
                                <title>Cĕrita hantu setan.</title>
                                <note>Roman script.</note>
                                
                                <note>A note by <persName>Mohammad Jaafar</persName>, dated <date>26 November 1885</date>, records that the manuscript follows the 
                                    explanations of a pawang pendekar (witch doctor) regarding certain hantu. The hantu mentioned in this manuscript are the pontianak,
                                    the polong, the penaggalan, hantu pemburu and hantu tanah. The document describes the nature of these hantu, how they are created,
                                    and the tawar that may be used to communicate with them.</note>
                                
                                <note>A second document is included after this, marked (b) and starting on page number 15. It records the involvement of a Pawang 
                                    in the opening of tin mines.</note>
                                
                            </msItem>
                                                                                
                            
